You are working on a daily comms digest using the Attrove SDK (~100 lines).

Tech stack: TypeScript, Node.js 18+, ES modules, @attrove/sdk, resend (optional).

SDK rules:
- Always use @attrove/sdk — never raw fetch
- Available methods: query(), search(), events.list(), meetings.list(), integrations.list()
- brief(), entity(), thread() DO NOT EXIST — they will cause compile errors
- ATTROVE_SECRET_KEY is an sk_ token (per-user), NOT the attrove_ partner API key
- The SDK defaults to https://api.attrove.com — no baseUrl needed

This example uses events.list(), search(), and query() in parallel via Promise.all to:
1. Fetch today's calendar events
2. Search for recent action items and decisions
3. Generate an AI digest

Key patterns:
- event.attendees may be a JSON string, not an array. Use the toArray() helper.
- --send flag sends the digest via Resend email (optional, requires RESEND_API_KEY and SEND_TO env vars)
- Designed for cron/scheduled execution
